library(sf)

ak_shp_sf = read_sf("shapefiles/ak_regions_simp.shp")
plot(ak_shp_sf)

To get the coordinate reference system:

st_crs(ak_shp_sf)
## Coordinate Reference System:
##   EPSG: 4326 
##   proj4string: "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs"

To change the projection system used the following. EPSG codes here.

ak_shp_sf = ak_shp_sf %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 3338)

st_crs(ak_shp_sf)
## Coordinate Reference System:
##   EPSG: 3338 
##   proj4string: "+proj=aea +lat_1=55 +lat_2=65 +lat_0=50 +lon_0=-154 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +ellps=GRS80 +towgs84=0,0,0,0,0,0,0 +units=m +no_defs"
plot(ak_shp_sf)

Spatial Joins

pop = read.csv("shapefiles/alaska_population.csv")

We need to transform .csv to sf file. When we transform it, we give the original crs code. Later we change to something else (i.e., same as above to be able to join them).

pop_sf = st_as_sf(pop,
                  coords = c("lng", "lat"),
                  crs = 4326,
                  remove = FALSE) %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 3338)
pop_joined_sf = st_join(pop_sf, ak_shp_sf, join = st_within)

plot(pop_joined_sf["region"])

Group by and summarize

pop_region = pop_joined_sf %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  group_by(region) %>% 
  summarize(total_pop = sum(population))

head(pop_region)
## # A tibble: 6 x 2
##   region           total_pop
##   <chr>                <int>
## 1 Aleutian Islands      8840
## 2 Arctic                8419
## 3 Bristol Bay           6947
## 4 Chignik                311
## 5 Cook Inlet          408254
## 6 Copper River          2294
ak_pop_sf = left_join(ak_shp_sf, pop_region)
## Joining, by = "region"
plot(ak_pop_sf["total_pop"])

ak_mgmt = ak_pop_sf %>% 
  group_by(mgmt_area) %>% 
  summarize(total_pop = sum(total_pop))

plot(ak_mgmt["total_pop"])

write_sf(ak_shp_sf, "shapefiles/ak_regions_population.shp")

Static plots

ggplot(ak_pop_sf) +
  geom_sf(data = ak_pop_sf, aes(fill = total_pop)) +
  geom_sf(data = pop_sf, size = 0.5) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(fill = "Total Population") +
  scale_fill_continuous(low = "khaki", high = "firebrick", labels = comma)

Interactive maps with leaflet

Section 19.6 of the tutorial.

In leaflet, we must use unprojected data.

epsg3338 <- leaflet::leafletCRS(
  crsClass = "L.Proj.CRS",
  code = "EPSG:3338",
  proj4def =  "+proj=aea +lat_1=55 +lat_2=65 +lat_0=50 +lon_0=-154 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +ellps=GRS80 +towgs84=0,0,0,0,0,0,0 +units=m +no_defs",
  resolutions = 2^(16:7))
ak_crs = st_transform(ak_pop_sf, crs = 4326)
pop_crs = st_transform(ak_pop_sf, crs = 4326)
pal = colorNumeric(palette = "Reds", domain = ak_crs$total_pop)

m = leaflet(options = leafletOptions(crs = epsg3338)) %>% 
  addPolygons(data = ak_crs,
              fillColor = ~pal(total_pop),
              weight = 1,
              color = "black",
              label = ~region,
              fillOpacity = 1)
